  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nThe \"Can not connect to mailserver\" popup shows multiples times, stacking over each other.\r\nThe longer the connection lost, the more popups show up.\r\n\r\nTo close those, you need to manually click on each \"Retry\" on each of them.\r\n\r\nAlso, when the connection is restored, the popups don't close automatically, which I would expect.\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25482501/170558389-32ba58db-e837-4f40-8a35-2315670d218c.mov\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nI get this behaviour after leaving the laptop closed for some time with the app launched.\r\nBut probably this can also be reproduced by just closing the internet connection.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen internet connection is lost, show a single notifying popup. And autoclose it, if the connection restored.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nWhen internet connection is lost, multiple popups show up overlaying each other.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: 0.5.0\r\n- Operating System: MacOS 12.4\r\n\r\n",
